PNB Housing Finance Ltd on Wednesday opened a regional office in Hyderabad and announced plans to add three more branches in south India by March.Inaugurating the new facility at Banjara Hills, Business Head Shaji Varghese said two of the branches would come up in Andhra Pradesh, at Vishakhapatnam and Vijayawada, while the other is to be opened in Kerala. With these, the number of branches in south India would touch nine this financial year.In the next fiscal, the company proposed to open 15 branches in the region. The network expansion, he explained, was part of the companyâ€™s focus on the south market and poised to help substantially grow the customer base in the region. Noting that Hyderabad real estate is a very important market, he said the regional office would cater to both Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.Upto September 30 in the current financial year, south India accounted for 24 per cent of the total loan book of Rs.5,310 crore. In 2014-15, the share of the region in the total disbursement was 23 per cent, a press release said.